National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice and Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism Lisa Monaco spoke with Afghan President Ashraf Ghani and Afghan National Security Advisor Hanif Atmar to express condolences for the recent attacks in Kabul. The attacks resulted in the deaths of over 40 Afghans, including women, children, and police cadets, as well as numerous injuries. Rice and Monaco conveyed the thoughts and prayers of the American people and reaffirmed U.S. support for Afghanistan in its fight against terrorism. They also expressed their commitment to the Afghan Government of National Unity and its efforts to achieve stability and security in the country.